The paper is about non-parallel voice conversion using CycleGAN, which involves deep learning techniques for speech processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing. The paper also involves improving the performance of the model, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves adversarial training, which falls under the category of generative models, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the model using objective and subjective measures, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible sub-category.
